{
  "message": "fuzz(cli-btrfs-parsers): 14 boundary seeds across length & value modes\n\nfuzz_cli_btrfs_parsers feeds each input byte stream through both\nffs-cli's btrfs root_item bytenr parser (184-byte structure with the\nu64 at 176..184) and the btrfs block-group total_bytes parser (16-byte\nstructure with the u64 at 8..16). The harness's build_payload sub-\nfunction reads `(len_mode, tail, body, value_mode, encoded)` for each\nparser, so a single input must satisfy 2\u00d7 that layout \u2014 meaning a\n3-seed corpus only ever exercised the simplest combinations.\n\nAdds 14 seeds that cover the full boundary matrix:\n\n  * happy paths: minimal valid (mode 1) for both, extended-tail\n    (mode 2) for both, smallest-nonzero (encoded=1) for both\n  * length errors: root truncated + bg valid, root valid + bg\n    truncated, both truncated (so the determinism + early-error\n    assertions hold even when every parser short-circuits)\n  * value errors: zero root bytenr (value_mode=0), zero bg\n    total_bytes (value_mode=0)\n  * boundary values: u64::MAX bytenr and u64::MAX total_bytes\n  * extended-buffer extremes: max tail (32 mod 33), zero tail\n    (mode 2 collapses to exact min_len)\n  * body-content variants: 0xFF-filled root body (verifies the\n    field-splatter overrides the body), realistic \"BGTOTAL\"\n    pattern in block-group body\n\nValidated by a 16 s libFuzzer run: 1.25 M executions, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
